"{\"uid\": \"si.com-olympics-2024-02-09-katie-ledecky-13-year-800-meter-freestyle-streak-ends-summer-mcintosh\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Katie Ledecky has dominated the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s swimming world for 13 years, but one of her most impressive streaks\\u00c2\\u00a0came to an end on Thursday.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 138, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Summer McIntosh defeated Ledecky in the 800-meter freestyle by six seconds at the\\u00c2\\u00a0Southern\\u00c2\\u00a0Zone South Sectional Championships in Orlando, the first time that Ledecky lost in this event since 2010.\", \"from\": 139, \"to\": 337, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 139, \"end\": 154, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Summer McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\"}, {\"begin\": 270, \"end\": 277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orlando_Magic\", \"score\": 0.9975239858996761, \"rank\": 0.0024821599612832685, \"text\": \"Orlando\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orlando_Magic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Orlando_Magic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s dominance in the event included three Olympics gold medals and eight more gold medals while competing in the World Championships and Pan Pacific Championships.\", \"from\": 339, \"to\": 510, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 484, \"end\": 509, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_Pacific_Swimming_Championships\", \"score\": 0.9999999999956799, \"rank\": 4.329862647386705e-12, \"text\": \"Pan Pacific Championships\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_Pacific_Swimming_Championships\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Pan_Pacific_Swimming_Championships\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She currently holds the women\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s world record for fastest time in the 800-meter freestyle, clocking in at 8:04:79 at the 2016 Olympics, and owns each of the 16 fastest times in the event.\", \"from\": 511, \"to\": 699, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky is still just 26 years old, and she will look to win her fourth 800-meter freestyle Olympic gold medal this Summer.\", \"from\": 701, \"to\": 824, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"McIntosh is only 17 years old, but the Canadian is already breaking through in the swimming world.\", \"from\": 826, \"to\": 924, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 826, \"end\": 834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 0.999999999972033, \"rank\": 2.7973073763363423e-11, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}, {\"begin\": 865, \"end\": 873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.5434058044001983, \"rank\": 0.785390171881127, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She competed in four events in the 2021 Summer Olympics, which included two fourth-place finishes and an 11th-place finish in the 800-meter freestyle.\", \"from\": 925, \"to\": 1075, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Since then, however, she\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s won eight medals, including four gold medals, in the last two World Aquatics Championshi